This documentation describes App Automator for PCF. It includes information about installing and configuring App Automator. It also describes how developers can define triggers and actions in App Automator to configure automated actions for apps.

## About App Automator for PCF

App Automator for PCF executes automated actions against apps based on triggers. For example, App Automator can automatically scale an app up or down when app metrics, such as memory or CPU, reach a given threshold. Developers can define custom actions and triggers in an App Automator manifest file. 

Operators can install App Automator for PCF on one or more spaces in a PCF deployment. For more information about installing and configuring App Automator, see [Using App Automator for PCF](../using.html).